article.headline: Drake 75, Bradley 73
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Drake used a second-half defensive stand to rally for a 75-73 win Thursday over Bradley -- its 100th win at the Knapp Center. The Bulldogs withstood a hot start from Bradley but held the Braves to 34 percent shooting after halftime. Nick Grant's two free throws with 53 seconds left gave Drake the lead permanently, and Al Stewart held the lead with four straight free throws. Drake (9-6, 2-2 Missouri Valley Conference) was 27-for-30 from the line. Chaun Brooks led the Bulldogs with 15 points. Stewart scored 14. Bradley (8-4, 2-2) suffered its 12th straight conference road loss. The Braves shot 57 percent in the first half for a 44-39 lead. Tony Bennett led the charge, scoring 21 of his 23 points before halftime. He was 7-for-7 from the field, including three 3-pointers.
